[2026-03-25] Perfect! I've pushed the fix (commit `c4eea59`). The solution uses a unified `_worker.js` file which is the recommended approach for Cloudflare Pages when you need to use external packages like `@neondatabase/serverless`.

**What changed:**
- ✅ Created `/functions/_worker.js` that handles ALL API routes in one file
- ✅ This approach lets Cloudflare properly bundle the `@neondatabase/serverless` package
- ✅ All your API endpoints (`/api/chat`, `/api/save-change`, etc.) are now routed through this

[2026-03-25] ✅ **Fixed!** Pushed commit `dd388e1`

**Problem:** `node_compat = true` is not supported in `wrangler.toml` for Cloudflare Pages projects.

**Solution:** Removed that line. The `compatibility_flags = ["nodejs_compat"]` is sufficient for enabling Node.js compatibility in Pages.

The deployment should now proceed successfully. Check your dashboard to confirm!

[2026-03-25] ✅ **Pushed commit `ccaa9cc`**

**What I fixed:**
- Removed the entire `functions/node_modules` directory (109 files deleted!)
- Removed the `postinstall` script from `package.json`
- Added `.cfignore` to prevent Cloudflare from processing unnecessary files

**Why this should work:**
- Cloudflare Pages will install `@neondatabase/serverless` from your root `package.json` during the build
- The `_worker.js` file will be bundled with the dependency properly
- No more TypeScript declaration file err

